      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming noise with a stationary fan on an AC unit usually points to a problem with the motor, which is probably seized up or has lost its power supply. It's not a good idea to just poke around in there without knowing what you're doing, especially if you're not familiar with electrical systems. You should definitely call a qualified HVAC technician, as messing with those components can be dangerous. A professional can diagnose whether it's a capacitor issue, a bad motor, or something else entirely.",
